-- Global Temperatures in August Above Average for 330th Month
-- B y   C h a r l o t t e   P o r t e r
-- 2012-09-17T15:01:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-17/global-temperatures-in-august-above-average-for-330th-month.html
August 2012 was the 330th month in
a row that global temperatures were above the 20th century
average, the U.S. National Climatic Data Center said.  Temperatures were above the average for the month in
northeastern  North America , central and southern Europe and
east-central Asia, the agency said today in a seasonal report.
Sea ice in the Arctic dropped to the lowest August level on
record.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Charlotte Porter at 
